The paper deals with the problem of classification in a statistical setting, which is a core topic in machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses data compression, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of VC dimension and sample complexity suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper deals with computable classification methods, which is a topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
